Description: Shoulder fragment of North Ionian black-figured pottery dinos or krater; interior: reserved; exterior, cream slip: much of sphinx facing right, left front paw raised; red additions on body, mane and wings; blobby filling ornaments; bordered above (tongues?) and below (added red line).
Curator's comments: The piece has been associated with 1888,0601.539a-b and d-e, but there is little to comfort the idea. Pencil '978'.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GG.1195)
